Richard Holmes goes on a journey through time to visit battlefields throughout Britain, northern France and Belgium that mark crucial moments in Britain's bloody and turbulent history 


1/6 Professor Richard Holmes retraces Henry V's route to Agincourt.

2/6 Professor Holmes visits the farms and fields where history hung in the balance.
 
3/6 Richard Holmes looks at the British retreat from Mons in 1914.
 
4/6 Richard Holmes walks through fields where the Battle of the Somme took place. 
 
5/6 Historian Richard Holmes reviews the strategic importance of the Battle for Arras in 1940.

6/6 Following the tanks of the 1944 British armoured break-out from the Normandy bridgehead.
 
 
 
 
 
1/6 Richard Holmes visits the site of William the Conqueror's historic victory 
 
2/6 Professor Richard Holmes visits the scene of Henry Tudor's victory over King Richard III. 

3/6 Richard Holmes travels to Naseby, where King Charles I lost the English Civil War.
